briefdescription.para: Determines whether attribute contains OIDs.
Specifies default value type.

detaileddescription.para: Default value can be a const assigned by switch (which is not known at compile), can be obtained by GET API, or a min/max value in specific range also assigned by switch at run time.
Default value can be also an object id.

briefdescription.para: Provides default value.

detaileddescription.para: If creation flag is CREATE_ONLY or CREATE_AND_SET then default value must be provided for attribute.

simplesect.para: Default value may not apply for ACL field or ACL entry, need special care.

briefdescription.para: Default value object type.

detaileddescription.para: Required when default value type is pointing to different object type.

briefdescription.para: Default value object id.

detaileddescription.para: Required when default value type is pointing to different object attribute.

briefdescription.para: Indicates whether default value needs to be saved.

detaileddescription.para: When switch is created some objects are created internally like vlan 1, vlan members, bridge port, virtual router etc. Some of those objects has attributes assigned by vendor like switch MAC address. When user changes that value then there is no way to go back and set it's previous value if user didn't query it first. This member will indicate whether user needs to query it first (and store) before change, if he wants to bring original attribute value later.
Some of those attributes can be OID attributes with flags MANDATORY_ON_CREATE and CREATE_AND_SET.

briefdescription.para: Indicates whether attribute is enum value.

detaileddescription.para: Attribute type must be set as INT32.

simplesect.para: Could be deduced from enum type string or enum vector values and attr value type.

briefdescription.para: Indicates whether attribute is enum list value.

detaileddescription.para: Attribute value must be set INT32 LIST.

simplesect.para: Could be deduced from enum type string or enum vector values and attr value type.

briefdescription.para: Provides enum metadata if attribute is enum or enum list.
Specifies condition type of attribute.

simplesect.para: Currently all conditions are "OR" conditions so we can deduce if this is conditional type if any conditions are defined.

briefdescription.para: Provide conditions for attribute under which this attribute will be mandatory on create.
Length of the conditions.
Indicates whether attribute is conditional.
Specifies valid only type of attribute.

simplesect.para: Currently all valid only are "OR" conditions so we can deduce if this is conditional type if any conditions are defined.

briefdescription.para: Provides conditions when this attribute is valid.

detaileddescription.para: If conditions are specified (OR condition assumed) then this attribute is only valid when different attribute has condition value set. Valid only attribute (against we check) can be dynamic so this attribute can't be marked as MANDATORY on create since default value will be required.

simplesect.para: There is only handful of attributes with valid only mark. For now we will check that in specific attribute logic.

briefdescription.para: Length of the valid only when conditions.
Indicates whether attribute is valid only.
When calling GET API result will be put in local db for future use (extra logic).

detaileddescription.para: This flag must be taken with care, since when set on dynamic attribute it may provide inconsistent data.
Value should be updated after successful set or remove.

Determines whether attribute value is primitive.

detaileddescription.para: Primitive values will not contain any pointers so value can be transferred by regular assignment operator.

briefdescription.para: Notification type.

detaileddescription.para: If attribute value type is POINTER then attribute value is pointer to switch notification. Enum sai_switch_notification_type_t is auto generated so it can't be used here, int will be used instead.

briefdescription.para: Is callback function.

detaileddescription.para: Set to true if attribute is callback function but not notification.

briefdescription.para: Pointer type.

detaileddescription.para: If attribute value type is POINTER then attribute value is pointer to switch. Enum sai_switch_pointer_type_t is auto generated so it can't be used here, int will be used instead.

briefdescription.para: Attribute capabilities.

detaileddescription.para: Represents attribute capability for each specific ASIC. Since each vendor may support different capabilities for each attribute, this field is optional. Also, since SAI API supports multiple switches (switch ids) at the same time, then switches may support different capabilities on different attributes. Vendor ID is provided inside capability struct for difference.
This data is designed for vendor internal usage.

briefdescription.para: Length of attribute capabilities.
Indicates whether attribute is extension attribute.
Tells if attribute is a resource type.

detaileddescription.para: If true, attribute is used in getting object type availability to distinguish between pools of resources.

briefdescription.para: Indicates whether attribute is deprecated.

detaileddescription.para: If true, attribute is deprecated and should not be used. Is up to vendor to check this field and give run time warning about this attribute.

briefdescription.para: Indicates whether condition is relaxed.

detaileddescription.para: If attribute is MANDATORY_ON_CREATE and relaxed flag is set to true then given attribute can be passed to create function even if the condition is not met. If relaxed flag is set to false, then attribute is forbidden to be passed to create function is condition is not met.

briefdescription.para: Indicates whether attribute is custom attribute.

detaileddescription.para: Custom attribute values begins with SAI_XXX_ATTR_CUSTOM_RANGE_START.

briefdescription.para: Specifies API version at which attribute was introduced.

detaileddescription.para: If no version is available, then this value will be SAI_VERSION(0,0,0).
This field should be used with nextrelease field.

briefdescription.para: Specified whether attribute will be present in next API release.

detaileddescription.para: It may happen that there are new attributes defined after stable release, and they will be part of next release. In this case API version will have value of current API version and nextrelease set to true.

For example, if attr is defined between v1.14 and v1.15, then API version will be v1.15 and next release is false. If attr is defined on top of v1.15 and there is not next release defined, then API version will be v1.15 and next release set to true.
